wiki.text:
The abbreviation 'RSD' may refer to:

* Serbian dinar, ISO 4217 code for the currency of Serbia
* RSD S.A., an information governance software provider
* Really Simple Discovery, an XML format describing some features of a
  blog service
* Recreational Software Designs, the developer of the seminal DOS-Based game
  creation system Game-Maker
* Reflex Sympathetic Dystrophy see Complex regional pain syndrome
* Remote Sensing Data, see Remote sensing - often information gathered by
  satellites
* Retinal Scanning Display, see Virtual retinal display
* Repetitive Stress Disorder, an old name for repetitive strain injury
* Relative standard deviation in statistics ( 'r<sub>sd</sub>' )
* Reichssicherheitsdienst (RSD) or Reich Security Service, personal bodyguards
  of Adolf Hitler
* RoadSide Delivery, a postal term used by Australia Post
* Robust Standard deviation, related to Standard deviation or Robust statistics
* Regulator of Sigma D, an anti-sigma factor against the major sigma factor
  (sigma70) in E. coli
* Record Store Day, an unofficial holiday celebrated by independent record
  stores in April.
* RSD-Gaskiya, or Social Democratic Rally, a political party of Niger
* Alias of Rob Smith, a British electronic musician
* Rubber Side Down, a cycling term meant to indicate keeping the wheels on the
  ground and not the other way around (i.e., don't crash).
